-Yes.

703
00:50:38,760 --> 00:50:42,230
-Thank you very much.
-Well, not just you, all of you.

704
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:44,516
-That's a nice gourd.
-What?

705
00:50:44,680 --> 00:50:46,796
-How much do you want for the gourd?
-You can have it.

706
00:50:46,960 --> 00:50:49,554
-Have it?
-Yes. Consider the lilies.

707
00:50:49,720 --> 00:50:51,836
-Don't you want to haggle?
-No. In the field.

708
00:50:52,000 --> 00:50:54,036
-What's wrong with it, then?
-Nothing, take it.

709
00:50:54,240 --> 00:50:57,073
-Consider the lilies?
-Well, the birds, then.

710
00:50:57,240 --> 00:50:58,719
-What birds?
-Any birds.

711
00:50:58,880 --> 00:51:01,838
-Why?
-Well, have they got jobs?

712
00:51:02,000 --> 00:51:03,513
-Who?
-The birds.

713
00:51:03,680 --> 00:51:05,398
Have the birds got jobs?!

714
00:51:05,600 --> 00:51:08,433
-What's the matter with him?
-He says the birds are scrounging.

715
00:51:08,600 --> 00:51:11,751
No, the point is the birds,
they do all right, don't they?

716
00:51:11,960 --> 00:51:14,520
-Well, and good luck to them!
-Yeah, they're very pretty.

717
00:51:14,720 --> 00:51:18,679
Okay. And you're much more
important than they are, right?

718
00:51:18,840 --> 00:51:21,115
So, what are you worrying about?
There you are! See?

719
00:51:21,480 --> 00:51:23,710
I'm worrying about what
you've got against birds.

720
00:51:24,280 --> 00:51:26,669
I haven't got anything against birds.
Consider lilies--

721
00:51:26,840 --> 00:51:29,752
-He's having a go at the flowers now.
-Give the flowers a chance.

722
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:31,911
-I'll give you one for it.
-It's yours!

723
00:51:32,080 --> 00:51:33,308
Two then.

724
00:51:33,480 --> 00:51:35,994
Look, there was this man,
and he had two servants--

725
00:51:36,200 --> 00:51:37,235
-What were they called?
-What?

726
00:51:37,400 --> 00:51:39,470
-What were their names?
-I don't know.

727
00:51:39,640 --> 00:51:40,993
And he gave them some talents--

728
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:43,469
-You don't know?
-Well, it doesn't matter.

729
00:51:43,640 --> 00:51:45,471
He doesn't know what they were called!

730
00:51:45,640 --> 00:51:47,676
Oh, they were called
Simon and Adrian. Now--

731
00:51:47,840 --> 00:51:49,159
You said you didn't know!

732
00:51:49,320 --> 00:51:51,880
It doesn't matter,
the point is there were two servants--

733
00:51:52,040 --> 00:51:54,793
-He's making it up as he goes along!
-No, I'm not!

734
00:51:54,960 --> 00:51:57,235
And he gave them--
Wait a minute, were there three?

735
00:51:57,400 --> 00:51:59,595
-He's terrible.
-There were three--

736
00:51:59,800 --> 00:52:02,951
-He's still a traitor!
-Oh, get off!

737
00:52:08,680 --> 00:52:11,433
Now hear this. Blessed are they...

738
00:52:11,600 --> 00:52:15,991
...who convert their neighbour's ox,
for they shall inhibit their girth.

739
00:52:16,160 --> 00:52:21,188
-Rubbish!
-And to them only shall be given....

740
00:52:21,360 --> 00:52:23,510
To them only...

741
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:27,232
...shall be given....

742
00:52:29,080 --> 00:52:30,593
What?

743
00:52:30,760 --> 00:52:33,479
-Shall be given what?
-Oh, nothing.

744
00:52:33,680 --> 00:52:35,272
-What were you going to say?
-Nothing.

745
00:52:35,440 --> 00:52:37,556
-You were going to say something.
-I finished.

746
00:52:37,720 --> 00:52:39,870
-Oh, no, no.
-Come on, tell us before you go.

747
00:52:40,080 --> 00:52:42,036
-I wasn't going to say anything.
-No, you hadn't.

748
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,997
-What won't he tell us?
-He won't say.

749
00:52:44,160 --> 00:52:45,513
-ls it a secret?
-No.

750
00:52:45,680 --> 00:52:47,591
-ls it?
-lt must be, otherwise he'd tell us.

751
00:52:47,760 --> 00:52:49,239
-Tell us.
-Leave me alone.

752
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:51,789
-What is the secret?
-ls it the secret of eternal life?

753
00:52:51,960 --> 00:52:52,949
He won't say!

754
00:52:53,120 --> 00:52:55,509
If I knew the secret
of eternal life, I wouldn't say.

755
00:52:55,680 --> 00:52:57,432
-Leave me alone.
-Just tell me, please.

756
00:52:57,600 --> 00:52:59,989
-No, tell us, master, we were here first.
-Rubbish!

757
00:53:00,160 --> 00:53:01,798
-Five!
-Go away!

758
00:53:01,960 --> 00:53:03,757
-Tell us, master.
-I can't go above 5.

759
00:53:03,920 --> 00:53:06,753
-ls that his gourd?
-Yes, but it's under offer.

760
00:53:06,920 --> 00:53:10,037
-This is his gourd.
-Ten!

761
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:15,149
It is his gourd.
We will carry it for you, master.

762
00:53:15,320 --> 00:53:16,878
Master?

763
00:53:17,040 --> 00:53:20,316
He's gone. He's been taken up.

764
00:53:20,480 --> 00:53:23,790
-Oh, he has been taken up!
-Eighteen!

765
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:25,552
No, there he is. Over there.

766
00:53:50,600 --> 00:53:52,352
Look!

767
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:56,748
-He has given us a sign.
-He has given us his shoe.

768
00:53:56,920 --> 00:53:59,559
The shoe is the sign!
Let us follow his example!

769
00:53:59,720 --> 00:54:02,234
-What?
-Let us, like him...

770
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:04,868
...hold up one shoe and let the other
be upon our foot...

771
00:54:05,040 --> 00:54:08,316
...for this is his sign that all who
follow him shall do likewise!

772
00:54:08,480 --> 00:54:13,349
No, no, the shoe is a sign that we must
gather shoes together in abundance.

773
00:54:13,520 --> 00:54:18,150
-Cast off the shoes. Follow the gourd!
-No, let us gather shoes together.

774
00:54:18,320 --> 00:54:19,833
-Let me!
-Oh, get off!

775
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:22,036
No, it is a sign that, like him,
we must think...

776
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:24,919
...not of the things of the body,
but of the face and head!

777
00:54:25,080 --> 00:54:27,833
-Give me your shoe!
-Get off!

778
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:31,037
Follow the gourd,
the holy gourd of Jerusalem!

779
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:33,998
-The gourd!
-Hold up the sandal, like he has--

780
00:54:34,160 --> 00:54:36,799
-lt is a shoe! It is a shoe!
-It's a sandal!

781
00:54:36,960 --> 00:54:39,838
-No, it isn't! It is a shoe!
-Cast it away!

782
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:41,399
-Put it on!
-Now clear off.

783
00:54:41,560 --> 00:54:43,551
Take the shoes and follow him!

784
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:48,840
Come all ye who call
yourselves Gourdenes.

785
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:51,432
Stop, I say.

786
00:54:51,600 --> 00:54:54,910
Stop. Let us....

787
00:54:55,080 --> 00:54:57,036
Let us pray.

788
00:54:57,200 --> 00:55:03,389
Yea, he cometh to us
like the seed to the grave....

789
00:55:24,280 --> 00:55:27,272
Master!

790
00:55:48,120 --> 00:55:51,999
Hey, is there another way down?

791
00:55:52,160 --> 00:55:55,835
Is there another path down to the river?

792
00:55:56,000 --> 00:55:57,956
Please, please, help me! I've got to get--

793
00:56:01,920 --> 00:56:04,480
My foot!

794
00:56:04,640 --> 00:56:08,076
-Damn! Damn! Damn!
-I'm sorry.

795
00:56:08,240 --> 00:56:11,676
-Damn! Damn and blast it!
-I'm sorry!

796
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:15,958
Don't you shush me. Eighteen years
of total silence, and you shush me.

797
00:56:16,120 --> 00:56:19,271
-What?
-I've kept my vow for 18 years.

798
00:56:19,440 --> 00:56:23,353
Not a single recognizable,
articulate sound has passed my lips.

799
00:56:23,520 --> 00:56:25,476
Please be quiet
for another five minutes.

800
00:56:25,640 --> 00:56:28,279
It doesn't matter now,
I might as well enjoy myself.

801
00:56:28,440 --> 00:56:31,830
The times in the last 18 years
I wanted to shout and sing...

802
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:35,276
...and scream my name out!
Oh, I'm alive!

803
00:56:42,160 --> 00:56:46,790
I'm alive! I'm alive!
Hello, birds! Hello, trees! I'm alive--

804
00:56:47,000 --> 00:56:48,558
Get off! I'm alive!

805
00:56:53,080 --> 00:56:56,311
Master! Master!

806
00:56:57,080 --> 00:56:59,992
The master! He is here!

807
00:57:00,160 --> 00:57:02,469
-The shoe!
-lt was the gourd!

808
00:57:02,640 --> 00:57:04,358
The shoe has brought us!

809
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:07,592
Speak! Speak to us, master!
Speak to us!

810
00:57:07,920 --> 00:57:12,072
-Go away!
-A blessing! A blessing!

811
00:57:12,240 --> 00:57:16,677
-How shall we go away, master?
-Just go away and leave me alone.

812
00:57:17,120 --> 00:57:18,633
Give us a sign.

813
00:57:18,800 --> 00:57:22,076
He has given us a sign,
he has brought us to this place!

814
00:57:22,280 --> 00:57:24,840
I didn't bring you here!
You just followed me!

815
00:57:25,040 --> 00:57:27,634
It's still a good sign,
by any standard.

816
00:57:27,800 --> 00:57:30,758
Master, your people have walked
many miles to be with you.

817
00:57:30,920 --> 00:57:32,672
They are weary and have not eaten.

818
00:57:32,880 --> 00:57:37,271
-It's not my fault they haven't eaten!
-There is no food in this high mountain.

819
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:40,438
What about the juniper bushes
over there?

820
00:57:41,160 --> 00:57:44,232
A miracle! A miracle!

821
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:47,790
He has made the bush
fruitful by his word!

822
00:57:47,960 --> 00:57:49,678
They brought forth juniper berries!

823
00:57:49,840 --> 00:57:52,957
Of course they brought forth
juniper berries, they're juniper bushes.

824
00:57:53,120 --> 00:57:54,235
What do you expect?!

825
00:57:54,440 --> 00:57:56,032
Show us another miracle.

826
00:57:56,200 --> 00:57:58,191
Do not tempt him, shallow ones!

827
00:57:58,360 --> 00:58:01,033
Is not the miracle
of the juniper bushes enough?

828
00:58:02,000 --> 00:58:05,788
-I say, those are my juniper bushes.
-They are a gift from God!

829
00:58:06,000 --> 00:58:08,309
They're all I've bloody got to eat.

830
00:58:08,480 --> 00:58:12,712
I say, get off of those bushes!
Go on! Clear off, the lot of you.

831
00:58:12,920 --> 00:58:18,119
-Lord, I am affected by a bald patch.
-I'm healed!

832
00:58:18,280 --> 00:58:21,113
-The master has healed me!
-I didn't touch him!

833
00:58:21,280 --> 00:58:23,669
I was blind, and now I can see!

834
00:58:23,840 --> 00:58:27,958
A miracle! A miracle! A miracle!

835
00:58:29,760 --> 00:58:34,390
Tell them to stop it. I hadn't said a word
for 18 years till he came along.

836
00:58:34,600 --> 00:58:38,070
A miracle! He is the Messiah!

837
00:58:38,280 --> 00:58:43,070
-And he hurt my foot!
-Hurt my foot, Lord! Hurt mine! Hurt mine!

838
00:58:43,240 --> 00:58:46,710
-Hail Messiah!
-I'm not the Messiah!

839
00:58:46,920 --> 00:58:50,037
I say you are, Lord.
And I should know, I've followed a few!

840
00:58:50,200 --> 00:58:53,476
-Hail Messiah!
-I'm not the Messiah!

841
00:58:53,640 --> 00:58:56,712
Would you please listen, I am not
the Messiah, do you understand?

842
00:58:56,880 --> 00:58:58,472
Honestly!

843
00:58:59,120 --> 00:59:02,749
Only the true Messiah denies his divinity.

844
00:59:02,960 --> 00:59:05,952
What? Well, what sort of chance
does that give me?

845
00:59:06,120 --> 00:59:11,877
-All right, I am the Messiah!
-He is! He is the Messiah!

846
00:59:12,080 --> 00:59:14,196
Now, fuck off!

847
00:59:21,640 --> 00:59:25,428
-How shall we fuck off, Lord?
-Just go away! Leave me alone!

848
00:59:25,640 --> 00:59:28,200
You told these people
to eat my juniper berries.

849
00:59:28,360 --> 00:59:31,158
You break my bloody foot,
you break my vow of silence...

850
00:59:31,320 --> 00:59:33,788
...and then you try and clean up
on my juniper bushes!

851
00:59:33,960 --> 00:59:37,794
Lay off! This is the Messiah,
the chosen one!

852
00:59:37,960 --> 00:59:40,793
-No, he's not.
-An unbeliever!

853
00:59:41,000 --> 00:59:42,149
An unbeliever!

854
00:59:42,360 --> 00:59:47,229
-Persecute! Kill the heretic!
-Yeah! Kill! Kill! Kill!

855
00:59:47,840 --> 00:59:50,638
-Kill!
-Leave him alone!

856
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:52,870
Leave him alone!

857
00:59:54,040 --> 00:59:55,109
Leave him alone.

858
00:59:55,320 --> 00:59:58,039
Put him down. Please!

859
01:00:01,720 --> 01:00:03,233
Brian?

860
01:00:03,400 --> 01:00:05,197
Judith?

861
01:00:49,640 --> 01:00:54,031
Look, there he is!
The chosen one has woken!

862
01:00:56,200 --> 01:00:57,428
Brian!

863
01:00:59,120 --> 01:01:00,758
Mother!

864
01:01:00,960 --> 01:01:04,191
-Brian!
-Hang on, Mother!

865
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:09,918
-Hello, Mother.
-Don't you "hello, Mother" me.

866
01:01:10,080 --> 01:01:12,548
-What are those people doing out there?
-Well, l....

867
01:01:12,720 --> 01:01:14,676
Come on! What have you
been up to, my lad?

868
01:01:14,840 --> 01:01:17,035
I think they must have
popped by for something.

869
01:01:17,200 --> 01:01:22,069
Popped by?! Swelled by, more like.
There's a multitude out there!

870
01:01:22,240 --> 01:01:23,878
They started following me yesterday.

871
01:01:24,040 --> 01:01:27,555
Well, they can stop following
you right now.

872
01:01:28,360 --> 01:01:32,751
Now stop following my son.
You ought to be ashamed of yourselves.

873
01:01:32,920 --> 01:01:37,391
The Messiah! The Messiah!
Show us the Messiah!

874
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:40,279
-The who?
-The Messiah!

875
01:01:41,040 --> 01:01:44,510
There's no Messiah in here.
There's a mess all right, but no Messiah.

876
01:01:44,680 --> 01:01:46,079
Now go away!

877
01:01:46,280 --> 01:01:48,271
Brian! Brian!

878
01:01:48,440 --> 01:01:50,670
Right, my lad,
what have you been up to?

879
01:01:50,880 --> 01:01:52,632
-Nothing, Mum.
-Come on, out with it.

880
01:01:52,800 --> 01:01:54,552
They think I'm the Messiah, Mum.

881
01:01:54,960 --> 01:01:57,076
-What have you been telling them?
-Nothing, l--

882
01:01:57,240 --> 01:02:00,073
-You're only making it worse for yourself.
-Look, I can explain--

883
01:02:00,240 --> 01:02:05,189
No, let me explain, Mrs. Cohen!
Your son is a born leader!

884
01:02:05,360 --> 01:02:08,636
Those people out there are following him
because they believe in him.

885
01:02:08,800 --> 01:02:10,438
They believe he can
give them hope.

886
01:02:10,600 --> 01:02:15,355
Hope of a new life,
a new world, a better future!

887
01:02:16,280 --> 01:02:19,590
-Who's that!?
-That's Judith, Mum.

888
01:02:19,760 --> 01:02:22,672
Judith, Mother.

889
01:02:25,800 --> 01:02:28,109
Show us the Messiah!

890
01:02:31,800 --> 01:02:34,792
Now you listen here,
he's not the Messiah!

891
01:02:34,960 --> 01:02:38,236
He's a very naughty boy! Now go away!

892
01:02:38,440 --> 01:02:42,194
-Who are you?
-I'm his mother, that's who.

893
01:02:42,400 --> 01:02:46,439
Behold his mother! Behold his mother!

894
01:02:46,600 --> 01:02:49,751
Hail to thee, mother of Brian!

895
01:02:49,920 --> 01:02:53,469
Blessed art thou! Hosanna!

896
01:02:53,640 --> 01:02:57,838
All things to thee, now and always!

897
01:02:58,040 --> 01:03:00,793
Now, don't think you can
get around me like that.

898
01:03:00,960 --> 01:03:04,430
He's not coming out,
and that's my final word.

899
01:03:05,280 --> 01:03:06,872
Now shove off!

900
01:03:07,080 --> 01:03:08,399
No!

901
01:03:09,320 --> 01:03:12,756
-Did you hear what I said?
-Yes!

902
01:03:13,200 --> 01:03:16,715
-Oh, I see. It's like that, is it?
-Yes!

903
01:03:17,920 --> 01:03:22,357
All right then, you can see him
for one minute, but not one second more!

904
01:03:22,520 --> 01:03:25,034
-Do you understand?
-Yes.

905
01:03:25,240 --> 01:03:29,119
-Promise?
-Well, all right.

906
01:03:29,680 --> 01:03:32,752
All right, here he is then.
Come on, Brian, come and talk to them.

907
01:03:32,920 --> 01:03:35,514
-But, Mum, Judith--
-Leave that Welsh tart alone.

908
01:03:35,680 --> 01:03:37,989
I don't really want to, Mum.

909
01:03:44,720 --> 01:03:47,996
-Good morning!
-A blessing! A blessing!

910
01:03:48,600 --> 01:03:52,912
No, please. Please, please, listen!

911
01:03:53,080 --> 01:03:55,674
I've got one or two things to say.

912
01:03:55,880 --> 01:03:58,189
Tell us! Tell us both of them!

913
01:03:58,680 --> 01:04:03,117
Look, you've got it all wrong!
You don't need to follow me.

914
01:04:03,280 --> 01:04:06,670
You don't need to follow anybody!

915
01:04:07,000 --> 01:04:11,516
You've got to think for yourselves.
You're all individuals!

916
01:04:11,680 --> 01:04:14,831
Yes, we're all individuals!

917
01:04:15,000 --> 01:04:16,911
You're all different.

918
01:04:17,120 --> 01:04:19,873
Yes, we are all different!

919
01:04:20,040 --> 01:04:22,031
I'm not.

920
01:04:22,880 --> 01:04:26,270
You've all got to work it out
for yourselves!

921
01:04:26,480 --> 01:04:30,393
Yes, we've got to work it
out for ourselves!

922
01:04:30,640 --> 01:04:32,551
Exactly!

923
01:04:32,720 --> 01:04:35,757
-Tell us more!
-No, that's the point!

924
01:04:35,920 --> 01:04:38,878
Don't let anyone tell you what to do!

925
01:04:39,040 --> 01:04:42,237
-Otherwise-- Oh, no!
-That's enough! That's enough.

926
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:47,436
That wasn't a minute.

927
01:04:47,600 --> 01:04:51,991
-Oh, yes, it was.
-Oh, no, it wasn't!

928
01:04:52,200 --> 01:04:54,873
Now stop that, and go away.

929
01:04:55,080 --> 01:04:57,036
-Excuse me?
-Yes?

930
01:04:57,240 --> 01:04:58,514
Are you a virgin?

931
01:04:59,200 --> 01:05:01,270
I beg your pardon?

932
01:05:01,640 --> 01:05:05,599
Well, if it's not a personal question,
are you a virgin?

933
01:05:05,800 --> 01:05:10,430
If it's not a personal question?!
How much more personal can you get?

934
01:05:10,600 --> 01:05:12,955
Now piss off.

935
01:05:14,280 --> 01:05:16,555
-She is.
-Must be. Definitely.

936
01:05:16,720 --> 01:05:19,154
