1014
01:09:26,200 --> 01:09:28,919
Obviously once the vote's been taken.
Can't act on a resolution--

1015
01:09:29,080 --> 01:09:31,275
-Reg, let's go now, please!
-Right! Right!

1016
01:09:31,440 --> 01:09:35,558
In the light of fresh information
from sibling Judith....

1017
01:09:35,720 --> 01:09:37,631
-Not so fast, Reg.
-Reg, for God's sake!

1018
01:09:37,800 --> 01:09:39,756
It's perfectly simple!

1019
01:09:39,920 --> 01:09:42,718
All you've gotta do is to go out
of that door now...

1020
01:09:42,920 --> 01:09:45,388
...and try to stop the Romans
nailing him up!

1021
01:09:45,560 --> 01:09:46,959
It's happening, Reg!

1022
01:09:47,120 --> 01:09:51,910
Something's actually happening, Reg!
Can't you understand?

1023
01:09:57,160 --> 01:10:00,630
-Yeah, hello.
-Another little ego trip from the feminists.

1024
01:10:00,800 --> 01:10:03,268
-What?
-Sorry, Loretta.

1025
01:10:03,440 --> 01:10:05,271
Read that back, would you?

1026
01:10:17,920 --> 01:10:19,319
Next.

1027
01:10:19,480 --> 01:10:20,833
-Crucifixion?
-Yes.

1028
01:10:21,000 --> 01:10:25,551
Good. Out of the door,
line on the left, one cross each.

1029
01:10:25,720 --> 01:10:26,914
Next.

1030
01:10:27,080 --> 01:10:28,274
Crucifixion?

1031
01:10:28,440 --> 01:10:33,753
Good. Out of the door, line on the left,
one cross each. Next.

1032
01:10:33,920 --> 01:10:36,798
-Crucifixion?
-No, freedom.

1033
01:10:36,960 --> 01:10:38,154
-What?
-Freedom for me.

1034
01:10:38,320 --> 01:10:42,472
They said I hadn't done anything
so I could go free and live on an island.

1035
01:10:43,640 --> 01:10:45,551
That's jolly good.
Well, off you go, then.

1036
01:10:45,720 --> 01:10:48,553
No, I'm only pulling your leg.
It's crucifixion, really.

1037
01:10:48,720 --> 01:10:50,472
I see. Very good, very good.

1038
01:10:50,640 --> 01:10:51,755
Well, out of the door.

1039
01:10:51,920 --> 01:10:54,229
Out of the door,
one cross each, line on the left.

1040
01:10:54,400 --> 01:10:57,392
Line on the left. Yes, thank you.
Crucifixion?

1041
01:10:57,560 --> 01:10:58,754
-Yes.
-Good.

1042
01:11:12,240 --> 01:11:15,152
People of Jerusalem!

1043
01:11:16,800 --> 01:11:19,633
Rome is your friend!

1044
01:11:24,480 --> 01:11:28,155
To prove our friendship,
it is customary at this time...

1045
01:11:28,320 --> 01:11:32,711
...to release a wrongdoer
from our prisons.

1046
01:11:36,480 --> 01:11:40,314
Whom would you have me release?

1047
01:11:40,480 --> 01:11:43,358
Release Roger!

1048
01:11:43,520 --> 01:11:47,149
Release Roger! Release Roger!

1049
01:11:49,880 --> 01:11:54,351
Very well, I shall release Roger!

1050
01:11:57,280 --> 01:11:59,396
Sir, we don't have a Roger, sir.

1051
01:11:59,560 --> 01:12:03,314
-What?
-We don't have anyone of that name, sir.

1052
01:12:03,480 --> 01:12:06,153
We have no Roger!

1053
01:12:09,000 --> 01:12:11,355
But what about Roderick, then?

1054
01:12:11,520 --> 01:12:15,035
Release Roderick! Release Roderick!

1055
01:12:15,200 --> 01:12:19,751
Centurion, why do they titter so?

1056
01:12:20,920 --> 01:12:23,514
Just some Jewish joke, sir.

1057
01:12:24,880 --> 01:12:27,872
