Who is this Roderick to whom you refer?

1063
01:12:47,120 --> 01:12:48,633
He is a robber!

1064
01:12:49,960 --> 01:12:52,599
And a rapist!

1065
01:12:53,000 --> 01:12:56,629
And a pickpocket!

1066
01:12:57,920 --> 01:12:59,672
He sounds a notorious criminal.

1067
01:12:59,840 --> 01:13:01,512
We haven't got him, sir.

1068
01:13:02,520 --> 01:13:04,238
Do we have anyone in our prisons?

1069
01:13:04,400 --> 01:13:06,152
-We've got a Samson, sir.
-Samson?

1070
01:13:06,320 --> 01:13:11,110
Samson the Sadducee Strangler, sir.
Silas the Syrian Assassin.

1071
01:13:11,280 --> 01:13:14,989
Several seditious scribes
from Caesarea.

1072
01:13:15,160 --> 01:13:16,149
Sixty-seven....

1073
01:13:16,320 --> 01:13:18,595
-Let me speak to them, Pontius!
-Oh, no!

1074
01:13:18,760 --> 01:13:20,193
Good idea, Biggus!

1075
01:13:20,360 --> 01:13:26,799
Citizens! We have Samson the Sadducee
Strangler, Silas the Assyrian Assassin...

1076
01:13:26,960 --> 01:13:30,794
...several seditious scribes
from Caesarea--

1077
01:13:30,960 --> 01:13:32,678
Next.

1078
01:13:33,120 --> 01:13:35,111
-Crucifixion?
-Yes.

1079
01:13:35,280 --> 01:13:39,319
Good. Out of the door,
line on the left, one cross each. Jailor?

1080
01:13:39,480 --> 01:13:42,995
-Excuse me? There's been a mistake--
-Just a moment, would you? Jailor?

1081
01:13:43,160 --> 01:13:46,948
-How many have come through?
-What?

1082
01:13:47,120 --> 01:13:49,839
How many have come through?

1083
01:13:50,000 --> 01:13:50,989
