1159
01:18:28,040 --> 01:18:29,075
What?

1160
01:18:29,240 --> 01:18:31,834
Don't worry about him sir,
he's ma--

1161
01:18:36,680 --> 01:18:39,990
-He's mad, sir.
-Have they gone?

1162
01:18:48,960 --> 01:18:51,838
-Oh, come on.
-Yes, sir.

1163
01:18:52,440 --> 01:18:56,194
-Anyway, get on with the story.
-Well, I just never really liked them, so l--

1164
01:18:57,280 --> 01:18:59,874
Right! The motion to get on with it
passed with one abstention.

1165
01:19:00,040 --> 01:19:02,395
I propose we go without further ado.
May I have a second?

1166
01:19:02,560 --> 01:19:04,630
-Let's just go.
-Yeah.

1167
01:19:19,640 --> 01:19:24,111
-Bloody Romans!
-Watch it! Still a few crosses left!

1168
01:19:25,760 --> 01:19:28,228
Up you go, big nose!

1169
01:19:28,400 --> 01:19:30,038
I'll get you for this, you bastard!

1170
01:19:30,200 --> 01:19:33,476
-Oh, yeah!
-Yeah, don't worry. I never forget a face.

1171
01:19:33,640 --> 01:19:35,153
-No?
-I warn you.

1172
01:19:35,320 --> 01:19:38,437
I'm gonna punch you so hard,
you Roman git!

1173
01:19:38,600 --> 01:19:40,670
Shut up, you Jewish turd!

1174
01:19:40,840 --> 01:19:44,753
Who are you calling Jewish?
I'm not Jewish, I'm a Samaritan!

1175
01:19:44,920 --> 01:19:47,718
A Samaritan? This is supposed
to be a Jewish section!

1176
01:19:47,880 --> 01:19:51,475
It doesn't matter!
You're all gonna die in a day or two!

1177
01:19:51,640 --> 01:19:54,916
It may not matter to you,
but it matters to us. Doesn't it, darling?

1178
01:19:55,080 --> 01:19:56,274
Oh, rather!

1179
01:19:56,440 --> 01:19:58,396
Under the terms
of the Roman occupancy...

1180
01:19:58,600 --> 01:20:01,478
...we're entitled to be crucified
in a purely Jewish area.

1181
01:20:01,640 --> 01:20:03,710
Pharisees separate from Sadducees!

1182
01:20:03,880 --> 01:20:05,916
And Swedish separate from Welsh!

1183
01:20:07,400 --> 01:20:10,790
All right, all right, all right!
We'll soon settle this!

1184
01:20:10,960 --> 01:20:16,273
Hands up, all those who
don't want to be crucified here!

1185
01:20:16,440 --> 01:20:18,192
Right! Next!

1186
01:20:18,360 --> 01:20:21,318
-Look, it's not my cross.
-What?

1187
01:20:21,480 --> 01:20:23,675
It's not my cross,
I was holding it for someone.

1188
01:20:23,840 --> 01:20:28,197
-Just lie down, I haven't got all day!
-Of course. Look, I hate to make a fuss--

1189
01:20:28,360 --> 01:20:31,352
Look, we've had a busy day,
and there's 140 of you lot to get up.

1190
01:20:31,520 --> 01:20:33,875
-ls he Jewish?
-Will you be quiet?!

1191
01:20:34,040 --> 01:20:36,076
We don't want more
Samaritans around here.

1192
01:20:36,240 --> 01:20:37,434
Belt up!

1193
01:20:37,600 --> 01:20:41,036
-Will you let me down if he comes back?
-Yeah, yeah, we'll let you down.

1194
01:20:41,200 --> 01:20:42,758
-Next!
-You don't have to do this!

1195
01:20:42,920 --> 01:20:46,879
-You don't have to take orders!
-I like orders.

1196
01:21:07,760 --> 01:21:10,433
See? Not so bad once you're up.

1197
01:21:11,360 --> 01:21:15,069
-You're being rescued then, are you?
-It's a bit late for that now, isn't it?

1198
01:21:15,240 --> 01:21:17,117
No, we've got a couple of days up here.

1199
01:21:17,280 --> 01:21:19,350
Plenty of time.
Lots of people get rescued.

1200
01:21:20,520 --> 01:21:22,556
Oh, yeah.
My brother usually rescues me.

1201
01:21:22,720 --> 01:21:25,439
If he can keep off the tail
for more than 20 minutes.

1202
01:21:25,600 --> 01:21:29,513
Randy little bugger.
Up and down like the Assyrian Empire.

1203
01:21:34,120 --> 01:21:36,395
Hello. Your family arrived then?

1204
01:21:36,560 --> 01:21:37,595
Reg!

1205
01:21:37,760 --> 01:21:40,911
-Hello, sibling Brian.
-Thank God you've come, Reg.

1206
01:21:41,080 --> 01:21:45,392
I think I should point out in fairness
that we are not the rescue committee.

1207
01:21:45,560 --> 01:21:48,393
However, I have been asked to read
this prepared statement...

1208
01:21:48,560 --> 01:21:50,198
...on behalf of the movement.

1209
01:21:50,360 --> 01:21:53,477
"We, the People's Front of Judea,
brackets, officials, end brackets...

1210
01:21:53,640 --> 01:21:57,952
...do hereby convey our sincere fraternal
and sisterly greetings to you, Brian...

1211
01:21:58,120 --> 01:22:01,237
-...on this occasion of your martyrdom."
-What?

1212
01:22:01,400 --> 01:22:04,870
"Your death will stand as a landmark
in the continuing struggle to liberate...

1213
01:22:05,040 --> 01:22:08,396
...the parent land from the hands
of the Roman imperialist aggressors...

1214
01:22:08,560 --> 01:22:11,677
...excluding those concerned with
drainage, medicine, roads, housing...

1215
01:22:11,840 --> 01:22:16,118
...education. And any other Romans
contributing to the welfare of Jews...

1216
01:22:16,280 --> 01:22:18,669
...of both sexes
and hermaphrodites."

1217
01:22:18,840 --> 01:22:21,638
Signed, "On behalf of the PF.J.,
et cetera."

1218
01:22:21,800 --> 01:22:24,792
And I'd just like to add, on
a personal note, my own admiration...

1219
01:22:24,960 --> 01:22:30,114
...for what you're doing for us and what
must be, after all, for you, a difficult time.

1220
01:22:30,280 --> 01:22:34,512
-Reg! What are you going to do?
-Goodbye, Brian. And thanks.

1221
01:22:36,320 --> 01:22:38,231
All right, Brian. Keep it up, lad.

1222
01:22:38,400 --> 01:22:40,709
Terrific work, Brian.

1223
01:22:45,800 --> 01:22:47,552
Right. And:

1224
01:22:47,720 --> 01:22:49,836
For he's a jolly good fellow

1225
01:22:50,000 --> 01:22:51,991
For he's a jolly good fellow

1226
01:22:52,160 --> 01:22:54,833
For he's a jolly good fellow

1227
01:22:55,000 --> 01:22:56,911
And so say all of us

1228
01:22:57,080 --> 01:22:59,640
And so say all of--

1229
01:23:02,600 --> 01:23:05,637
You bastards! You bastards!

1230
01:23:05,800 --> 01:23:08,792
-Where is Brian of Nazareth?
-You sanctimonious bastards!

1231
01:23:08,960 --> 01:23:12,714
-I have an order for his release.
-You stupid bastards!

1232
01:23:12,880 --> 01:23:14,836
-I'm Brian of Nazareth.
-What?

1233
01:23:15,000 --> 01:23:16,638
-I'm Brian of Nazareth.
-Take him down!

1234
01:23:16,800 --> 01:23:18,438
I'm Brian of Nazareth!

1235
01:23:19,040 --> 01:23:21,554
-I'm Brian!
-I'm Brian!

1236
01:23:21,720 --> 01:23:23,517
Look, look, I'm Brian!

1237
01:23:23,680 --> 01:23:26,638
-I'm Brian!
-I'm Brian and so is my wife!

1238
01:23:29,600 --> 01:23:33,991
-Right! Take him away and release him!
-No, I'm only joking. I'm not really Brian.

1239
01:23:34,160 --> 01:23:37,232
No, I'm not Brian! I was only--
It was a joke.

1240
01:23:37,400 --> 01:23:39,868
I'm only pulling your leg!
It's a joke!

1241
01:23:40,040 --> 01:23:42,349
I'm not him,
I'm just having you on!

1242
01:23:42,520 --> 01:23:46,069
Put me back!
Bloody Romans, can't take a joke.

1243
01:23:55,600 --> 01:23:57,318
The Judean People's Front!

1244
01:23:58,320 --> 01:24:00,595
The Judean People's Front!

1245
01:24:00,760 --> 01:24:04,389
Forward, all!

1246
01:24:07,440 --> 01:24:12,389
-Look out! The Judean People's Front!
-The Judean People's Front!

1247
01:24:12,560 --> 01:24:15,074
The Judean People's Front!

1248
01:24:18,960 --> 01:24:23,954
We are the Judean People's Front,
crack suicide squad.

1249
01:24:24,120 --> 01:24:28,238
Suicide squad, attack!

1250
01:24:36,440 --> 01:24:39,318
That showed them, huh?

1251
01:24:40,080 --> 01:24:42,469
You silly sods!

1252
01:24:42,640 --> 01:24:44,312
Brian!

1253
01:24:48,160 --> 01:24:50,116
Judith!

1254
01:24:50,280 --> 01:24:55,832
Terrific! Great! Reg explained it to me,
and I think it's great what you're doing.

1255
01:24:56,000 --> 01:25:00,232
Thank you, Brian. I'll never forget you.

1256
01:25:08,200 --> 01:25:10,794
So there you are!

1257
01:25:10,960 --> 01:25:13,110
I might have known
it would end up like this.

1258
01:25:13,280 --> 01:25:17,114
Just think of all the love
and affection I've wasted on you!

1259
01:25:17,280 --> 01:25:19,874
Well, if that's how you treat
your poor, old mother...

1260
01:25:20,040 --> 01:25:23,316
...in the autumn years of her life,
all I can say is:

1261
01:25:23,480 --> 01:25:27,359
Go ahead. Be crucified.
See if I care.

1262
01:25:27,520 --> 01:25:32,355
-I might have known.
-Mum! Mum!

1263
01:25:32,520 --> 01:25:34,590
I don't know what
the world is coming to.

1264
01:25:39,680 --> 01:25:41,159
Cheer up, Brian!

1265
01:25:41,320 --> 01:25:43,436
You know what they say?

1266
01:25:43,600 --> 01:25:46,273
Some things in life are bad.

1267
01:25:46,440 --> 01:25:48,954
They can really make you mad.

1268
01:25:49,120 --> 01:25:52,874
Other things just make
you swear and curse.

1269
01:25:53,040 --> 01:25:55,315
When you're chewing on life's gristle

1270
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:58,756
Don't grumble
Give a whistle

1271
01:25:58,920 --> 01:26:03,152
And this'll help things
Turn out for the best

1272
01:26:03,320 --> 01:26:04,912
And

1273
01:26:05,080 --> 01:26:10,950
Always look on the bright side of life

1274
01:26:13,120 --> 01:26:18,478
Always look on the light side of life

1275
01:26:20,080 --> 01:26:22,071
If life seems jolly rotten

1276
01:26:22,240 --> 01:26:23,958
There's something you've forgotten

1277
01:26:24,120 --> 01:26:27,669
And that's to laugh and smile
And dance and sing

1278
01:26:27,840 --> 01:26:29,592
When you're feeling in the dumps

1279
01:26:29,760 --> 01:26:31,876
Don't be silly chumps

1280
01:26:32,040 --> 01:26:34,952
Just purse your lips and whistle
That's the thing

1281
01:26:35,120 --> 01:26:41,309
And always look on
The bright side of life

1282
01:26:41,480 --> 01:26:43,277
Come on!

1283
01:26:43,640 --> 01:26:48,555
Always look on the right side of life

1284
01:26:51,120 --> 01:26:52,838
For life is quite absurd

1285
01:26:53,000 --> 01:26:54,672
And death's the final word

1286
01:26:54,840 --> 01:26:58,435
You must always face
The curtain with a bow

1287
01:26:58,600 --> 01:27:00,397
Forget about your sin

1288
01:27:00,560 --> 01:27:02,551
Give the audience a grin

1289
01:27:02,720 --> 01:27:05,678
Enjoy it
It's your last chance anyhow

1290
01:27:05,840 --> 01:27:11,312
So always look on
The bright side of death

1291
01:27:14,440 --> 01:27:18,956
Just before
You draw your terminal breath

1292
01:27:22,000 --> 01:27:23,752
Life's a piece of shit

1293
01:27:23,920 --> 01:27:25,638
When you look at it

1294
01:27:25,800 --> 01:27:29,349
Life's a laugh and death's a joke
It's true

1295
01:27:29,520 --> 01:27:31,158
You'll see it's all a show

1296
01:27:31,320 --> 01:27:33,117
Keep 'em laughing as you go

1297
01:27:33,280 --> 01:27:36,795
Just remember that
The last laugh is on you

1298
01:27:36,960 --> 01:27:42,990
And always look on
The bright side of life

1299
01:27:45,240 --> 01:27:50,030
Always look on the right side of life

1300
01:27:50,200 --> 01:27:52,794
Come on, Brian! Cheer up!

1301
01:27:52,960 --> 01:27:58,318
Always look on the bright side of life

1302
01:28:00,480 --> 01:28:05,076
Always look on the bright side of life

1303
01:28:05,240 --> 01:28:08,038
Worse things happen at sea,
you know?

1304
01:28:08,200 --> 01:28:11,192
Always look on the bright side of life

1305
01:28:11,360 --> 01:28:13,669
What have you got to lose?
You come from nothing...

1306
01:28:13,840 --> 01:28:15,751
...you're going back to nothing,
what have you lost?

1307
01:28:15,920 --> 01:28:17,239
Nothing!

1308
01:28:20,880 --> 01:28:23,474
Nothing will come from nothing,
you know what they say?

1309
01:28:23,640 --> 01:28:25,153
Cheer up, you old bugger!

1310
01:28:25,320 --> 01:28:27,788
Come on! Give us a grin!
There you are!

1311
01:28:27,960 --> 01:28:32,909
See? The end of the film. Incidentally,
this record is available in the foyer.

1312
01:28:33,600 --> 01:28:36,831
Some of us have got to live
as well, you know?

1313
01:28:37,000 --> 01:28:39,833
Who do you think pays
for all this rubbish?

1314
01:28:40,000 --> 01:28:42,514
They're not gonna make
their money back, you know.

1315
01:28:42,680 --> 01:28:44,352
I told them. I said to him.

1316
01:28:44,520 --> 01:28:47,796
"Bernie," I said,
"They'll never make their money back."

